    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-04-01T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-04-01T05:00:00-05:00" n="492"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d492">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">251.11 Insull, Samuel/463: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Skinner</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Ankara</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-04-01T12:00:00+02:00"
                            >April 1, 1934—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received April 1—9:45 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>25. <hi rend="italic">Maiotis</hi> with Insull still in port. All now depends on
                    the rapidity with which the court acts and its acceptance of our indictment as
                    adequate. The Greek Government has protested against the detention of the ship.
                    The Turkish Government has replied that ship is free and remains
                    voluntarily.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Skinner</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
